Here is the complete, detailed implementation plan for adding dark/light mode to the AstroLab web app.

---

## Design Decisions Summary

### Decision 1: CSS Strategy -- Pure CSS Variable Toggle (NOT Tailwind `darkMode: 'class'`)

The codebase already uses CSS custom properties (`var(--color-*)`) throughout nearly all components. The most efficient strategy is to override these variables under an `html.dark` selector. This means components that already reference `var(--color-bg)`, `var(--color-surface)`, `var(--color-text)`, etc. will automatically adapt with zero code changes.

This avoids the Tailwind `darkMode: 'class'` approach which would require adding `dark:` prefixed utility classes to every single element in 70+ files -- a massive and unnecessary refactoring effort.

### Decision 2: Hardcoded Colors -- Add New Structural CSS Variables, Leave Semantic Colors As-Is

The hardcoded Tailwind colors fall into two categories:

**Structural/neutral colors (MUST fix):** `border-slate-200`, `bg-slate-50`, `hover:bg-slate-100`, `bg-indigo-50`, `bg-slate-200`, `border-slate-300`. These are used for borders, hover states, active states, and skeletons. They must change in dark mode or the UI will have jarring white/light patches on a dark background.

**Semantic status colors (leave for now):** `bg-green-100 text-green-700`, `bg-red-600`, `text-red-600`, etc. These convey meaning (success, error, warning). They work acceptably on dark backgrounds and would require disproportionate effort to make perfect. They can be refined in a later pass.

New CSS variables to add: `--color-border`, `--color-hover`, `--color-active` (for indigo-50 equivalent), `--color-skeleton`.

### Decision 3: Toggle Placement

**MerchantNav (sidebar):** Place the toggle in the bottom section of the desktop sidebar, between the divider and the business name/logout area. This is the "settings zone" of the sidebar. In the mobile overlay menu, add it at the bottom.

**CustomerNav (top bar):** Place the toggle in the right side area of the desktop navbar, before the user avatar. On mobile top bar, place it before the avatar.

### Decision 4: ThemeProvider Position

`ThemeProvider` should be the **outermost** provider in `App.tsx`, wrapping `AuthProvider`. It has no dependencies on auth state and must be available on non-authenticated pages (Landing, Login, etc.).

---

## Implementation Plan: File-by-File

### Phase 1: Infrastructure (4 files)

---

#### File 1: `apps/web/src/styles/globals.css`

**What to change:** Add dark mode variable overrides, new structural variables for both modes, and a transition helper class.

**Exact changes:**

Add new structural variables inside the existing `:root` block:
```css
:root {
  /* existing vars stay unchanged */
  --color-primary: #6366f1;
  --color-primary-dark: #4f46e5;
  --color-secondary: #f59e0b;
  --color-bg: #f8fafc;
  --color-surface: #ffffff;
  --color-text: #1e293b;
  --color-text-muted: #64748b;

  /* NEW structural vars for light mode */
  --color-border: #e2e8f0;       /* slate-200 */
  --color-hover: #f1f5f9;        /* slate-100 */
  --color-active: #eef2ff;       /* indigo-50 */
  --color-skeleton: #e2e8f0;     /* slate-200 */
}
```

Add a new `html.dark` block after `:root`:
```css
html.dark {
  --color-primary: #818cf8;      /* indigo-400, brighter for dark bg */
  --color-primary-dark: #6366f1; /* indigo-500 */
  --color-secondary: #fbbf24;    /* amber-400, brighter for dark bg */
  --color-bg: #0f172a;           /* slate-900 */
  --color-surface: #1e293b;      /* slate-800 */
  --color-text: #f1f5f9;         /* slate-100 */
  --color-text-muted: #94a3b8;   /* slate-400 */
  --color-border: #334155;       /* slate-700 */
  --color-hover: #334155;        /* slate-700 */
  --color-active: #312e81;       /* indigo-900 */
  --color-skeleton: #334155;     /* slate-700 */
}
```

Add a transition helper class at the end of the file:
```css
html.theme-transition,
html.theme-transition *,
html.theme-transition *::before,
html.theme-transition *::after {
  transition: background-color 0.3s ease,
              color 0.3s ease,
              border-color 0.3s ease,
              box-shadow 0.3s ease !important;
}
```

This class is added briefly during theme toggle (managed by ThemeContext) and removed after 300ms to prevent initial page load transitions.

---

#### File 2: `apps/web/src/contexts/ThemeContext.tsx` (NEW FILE)

**Create this file** following the exact AuthContext pattern:

```tsx
import {
  createContext,
  useState,
  useEffect,
  useCallback,
  type ReactNode,
} from 'react';

type Theme = 'light' | 'dark';

export interface ThemeContextValue {
  theme: Theme;
  toggleTheme: () => void;
  isDark: boolean;
}

export const ThemeContext = createContext<ThemeContextValue | null>(null);

const STORAGE_KEY = 'astrolab-theme';

function getSystemTheme(): Theme {
  return window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches
    ? 'dark'
    : 'light';
}

function getInitialTheme(): Theme {
  const stored = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY) as Theme | null;
  if (stored === 'light' || stored === 'dark') return stored;
  return getSystemTheme();
}

function applyTheme(theme: Theme) {
  const root = document.documentElement;
  if (theme === 'dark') {
    root.classList.add('dark');
  } else {
    root.classList.remove('dark');
  }
}

export function ThemeProvider({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {
  const [theme, setTheme] = useState<Theme>(getInitialTheme);

  // Apply theme on mount and changes
  useEffect(() => {
    applyTheme(theme);
  }, [theme]);

  // Listen for system preference changes (only when no manual override)
  useEffect(() => {
    const mq = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)');
    const handler = (e: MediaQueryListEvent) => {
      const stored = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);
      if (!stored) {
        setTheme(e.matches ? 'dark' : 'light');
      }
    };
    mq.addEventListener('change', handler);
    return () => mq.removeEventListener('change', handler);
  }, []);

  const toggleTheme = useCallback(() => {
    // Add transition class for smooth switch
    document.documentElement.classList.add('theme-transition');
    setTimeout(() => {
      document.documentElement.classList.remove('theme-transition');
    }, 300);

    setTheme((prev) => {
      const next = prev === 'dark' ? 'light' : 'dark';
      localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, next);
      return next;
    });
  }, []);

  const value: ThemeContextValue = {
    theme,
    toggleTheme,
    isDark: theme === 'dark',
  };

  return (
    <ThemeContext.Provider value={value}>{children}</ThemeContext.Provider>
  );
}
```

Key implementation details:
- `getInitialTheme()` checks localStorage first, then system preference, defaulting to light.
- `applyTheme()` adds/removes the `dark` class on `<html>`.
- The `theme-transition` class is applied for 300ms during toggles for smooth color transitions.
- System preference changes are listened to only when no manual override exists in localStorage.

---

#### File 3: `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` (NEW FILE)

Following the exact `useAuth.ts` pattern:

```ts
import { useContext } from 'react';
import { ThemeContext, type ThemeContextValue } from '../contexts/ThemeContext';

export function useTheme(): ThemeContextValue {
  const ctx = useContext(ThemeContext);
  if (!ctx) {
    throw new Error('useTheme doit etre utilise dans un ThemeProvider');
  }
  return ctx;
}
```

