## FOUC (Flash of Unstyled Content) Prevention

To prevent a flash of light mode before React hydrates:

Add a tiny inline script in `apps/web/index.html` inside `<head>`, before any CSS loads:

```html
<script>
  (function() {
    var theme = localStorage.getItem('astrolab-theme');
    if (theme === 'dark' || (!theme && window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches)) {
      document.documentElement.classList.add('dark');
    }
  })();
</script>
```

This runs synchronously before any rendering, ensuring the correct class is on `<html>` from the very first paint.

